    "Finally, Strengths and Limitations (Section 6) and Conclusion (Section 7) are reported.",
    "Schema and media framing theory.",
    "The well-known schema theory [50] [51] [52] in brief affirms that, schemas are organized knowledge stored in the minds that people develop by interacting with the environment through the assimilation process [50, 53].",
    "They regard declarative -i.e., knowledge of what is an object, a fact, or an event -and procedural knowledge -i.e., knowledge of how to perform an action or behavior- [54].",
